What you need to know:

The company Thursday took rally enthusiasts down memory lane when it unveiled the 1985 Toyota Celica Twincam Turbo which was driven to victory by Juha KankkunenThe Celica now stands side by side with the 2019 FIA World Championship winning Toyota Yaris WRC replica in a well-choreographed marketing blitz to raise Toyota’s profile as “King of Africa"Kankkunen, also the winner in 1991 and 1993 Safari editions, will grace this year’s event expected to be held between June 24-27 in Nairobi and Naivasha as a special guest of the WRC Safari Rally Kenya